Legendary post-punk group The Cassandra Complex will celebrate their 40 year anniversary with an extensive world tour spanning Europe and the Americas. 

Originating in the mid-eighties, The Cassandra Complex swiftly garnered attention for their distinct fusion of electronics, post-punk aesthetics, guitar-driven soundscapes, and the commanding vocals of Rodney Orpheus. Tracks such as "Moscow Idaho," "One Millionth Happy Customer," and "The War Against Sleep" catapulted them to fame across Europe. Extensive tours solidified their position as one of the foremost post-punk bands of their time.

Rodney Orpheus has also worked in the field of music technology helping to create and promote much of the tech that musicians around the world use today, particularly VST (Virtual Studio Technology) which revolutionized the music industry. He has worked with artists as diverse as Kevin Godley (10cc, Godley & Creme), Sinead O‚ÄôConnor, The Sisters of Mercy, Die Krupps, and Future Sound of London.

name: Lagum | Dublin | Button Factory
address: {'address': 'Curved St, Temple Bar, Dublin, Ireland', 'zip_code': None}
description:
After releasing the album "After the End" - nominated for the Latin Grammy, with several sold-out dates in 2023 and a European tour, in 2024, Lagum continues on the road with the "Lagum Live" tour. 

"Our band was born on stage, and only then did we start recording music. What I want the most is to get people out of their homes to watch our show because that's when we're truly ourselves. On December 14th, we will release our first Live Album with the recording of our show in S√£o Paulo, so you can already feel the energy of what's to come," says Pedro Calais, the band's vocalist. 

With a repertoire that includes Lagum's greatest hits and the songs that fans identify with the most, the performance celebrates the band's journey and demonstrates the energy of rock that is not always fully captured in studio versions. During the show, the band also allows for improvisation and includes the members' favorite songs.

Strictly over 18 years of age. Tickets non-refundable.

name: King Kong Fran | Dublin
address: {'address': "8 Leeson Street Lower, Saint Kevin's, Dublin, D02 ET97, Ireland", 'zip_code': 'D02 ET97'}
description:
6pm: Doors
7pm: Showtime

A critical and popular success throughout Brazil, the show/performance King Kong Fran, by actress and clown Rafaela Azevedo, arrives in Dublin on Tuesday, February 11 2025, at The Sugar Club. Combining cabaret, circus, and a 'gorilla woman' act, the show presents the character Fran, who subverts feminine stereotypes, creating a reflection full of humour and irony on themes such as sexism, harassment, abuse, and consent. She interacts with the audience, making men 'taste their own medicine.

Get ready for an unforgettable evening! We are thrilled to invite you to our first big event of the year in Barcelona on December 13th, 2024. It‚Äôs the perfect way to kick off the year in style, surrounded by amazing vibes, open-minded individuals, and an electric atmosphere.

! Win FREE Entry to ALL Our Events in 2025 !
For the first time ever, we‚Äôre hosting an exclusive competition, and three lucky winners will receive a FREE pass to all our events throughout 2025.

Here‚Äôs how it works:

How to Participate:
You must be physically present at the event on December 13th to join the competition.
Upon entering the venue, you‚Äôll receive a unique number at the registration desk.
To receive your number, you must arrive before 23:00, so don‚Äôt be late!

The Draw:
Around 1:00 AM, one of our team members will take the stage and use a randomizer tool displayed on the big screen to select three winning numbers.
If your number is drawn, you‚Äôll be invited to the stage to receive a personalized certificate that grants you FREE entry to all our 2025 events.

Dive into the Sexy Techno Beats of Our Night

Join us for an unforgettable evening where freedom of expression reigns supreme. This is your safe space to explore, connect, and dance under electrifying beats in an atmosphere that celebrates individuality and boldness.

Dress Code:
Unleash your creativity and come dressed to impress. Latex, leather, and daring outfits are highly encouraged. Let your outfit reflect your inner desires.
No jeans, streetwear, or casual clothing. This night is all about sensuality and style.

Be bold. Be free. Be yourself!

name: Desires Presents: Voigtmann
address: {'address': '74 Lower Alabama Street, Atlanta, GA 30303, USA', 'zip_code': '30303'}
description:
As co-founder of Toi.Toi.Musik, one of London‚Äôs most conceptual and future-facing parties, Claus Voigtman‚Äôs contribution to the enduring relevance of Djing is second-to-none. With a genuinely humble dedication to the craft and to producing music of his own, he‚Äôs quietly yet confidently acquired the respect of his peers in what is, in music terms, a remarkably short time. After having completed his mission withToi.Toi.Musik, he went off seeking new exciting and challenging musical journeys with his new love
Subsequent.

Patience defines Voigtmann‚Äôs outlook; never one to rush things. He‚Äôs issued just a handful releases under his own name since 2013 with each exceeding the other in terms of quality. It‚Äôs an apt descriptor of his mixing style too. He‚Äôs reserved and restrained, taking pride in providing moments of ecstatic euphoria only when strictly necessary, doubling their effectiveness as a result. It‚Äôs what he chooses not to include that makes him such a devastating capable selector. Coming from a punk band background, he rocks his sets with that certain punk attitude and never ceases to move the floor. Groove and funk are ever present.

The world has taken notice, too. Voigtmann regularly enjoys sets at Fabric, Rex Club, Off-Sonar, Festivals, South - and North-America and many settings the world over. He‚Äôs the kind of artist who will actively endeavor to never stop learning. To Voigtmann, music cannot be quantified, and as such, can never be completed. His journey as a student of music will never end. An Architect, designer Dj, and producer, he is respectful yet fearless and defiant of trends and hype.

name: No Sleep Presents: Ma Haiping & Elias Garcia
description:
No Sleep is honored to welcome Shanghai-based techno artist Ma Haiping (Axis/Molecular) to Boston as part of his debut US tour, alongside the familiar heavy-hitter Elias Garcia. Known for their hypnotic sound with influences from science fiction, both artists have been responsible for creating some of our favorite techno tracks.

Ma's productions are regularly played in performances by some of the world's most talented DJs, and this December we plan to show you why.

Sunday, December 15th
9PM - 2AM
Hennessy's (Upstairs)
25 Union St. Boston
21+

MA HAIPING:

Ma Haiping stands as one of China‚Äôs most influential electronic and independent musicians.

Lauded by Jeff Mills, his album ‚ÄúChang‚Äôe-4‚Äù was released on the legendary Axis Records, marking a significant milestone in his career. In recent years, his music has garnered widespread international acclaim, seamlessly blending the traditions of Detroit Techno with Sci-Fi and Hypnotic elements to create futuristic tracks designed for the dance floor.

In 2013, Ma Haiping made history by becoming the first Chinese producer to release Techno in Detroit with his EP ‚ÄúThe Chinese Connection‚Äù on Scan 7‚Äôs Cratesaves International label. His journey continued in 2015 with the release of the EP ‚ÄúCrepuscular Rays‚Äù on Orlando Voorn‚Äôs Nightvision label. Between 2022 and 2024, he released several EPs, including ‚ÄúXX 8,‚Äù ‚ÄúCollapse,‚Äù ‚ÄúParallel Cycle,‚Äù ‚ÄúInvincible EP‚Äù and ‚ÄúArtificial Ecstatic‚Äù across various prestigious labels such as the UK‚Äôs Molecular Recordings, France‚Äôs Seclusion, and the USA‚Äôs Sythetik Sound.

His tracks have been frequently featured by Beatport as the best Techno (R/D/H) tracks of the month. Esteemed media outlets like Groove Mag, Mixmag (UK and Asia editions), and 5 Magazine have recommended his work. Ma Haiping‚Äôs music is regularly played by top international artists, including Jeff Mills, Richie Hawtin, Slam, Ben Sims, Ken Ishii, DVS1, R√∏dh√•d, Kr!z, and Rene Wise in their DJ performances.

ELIAS GARCIA:

Producer, DJ and Sceptre Records founder Elias Garcia was born in the Bronx, New York, and has been a musician since childhood. Music became a cornerstone of his identity. As a resident DJ for the United States techno collective Infra Boston, Elias has played for others such as Oclock Porto, Stamina FL, Shift NY, Future Arkive, Infra Boston, III Points Festival, Fader Events & WeAreAllVast in Portland. His productions have been supported by artists such as Oscar Mulero, DVS1 & Kr!z from his label releases such as Modularz, Voyager & Codec: His productions delve into the eerie, hypnotic, and mysterious musical structures of electronic music, which became critical to his science fiction-influenced sound.

Limited to just 30 guests per session, Bedchamber Jam is not just an event‚Äîit‚Äôs boundary-breaking cultural alchemy, staged in a boutique hotel‚Äôs secret corner for those seeking something edgy, intimate, and different.

name: Zeyzey Presents: Satin Jackets + Supertaste (Dj Set)
description:
Formed in 2012 Satin Jackets is the brainchild of German producer Tim Bernhardt. Having enjoyed success throughout the late 90s and 00s producing house music under a variety of different aliases, Tim launched Satin Jackets as a vehicle to finally explore his lifelong love of disco. 

Whilst the face behind the Satin Jackets mask may have remained a mystery his warm sound has fast become very familiar to music lovers around the world. His debut album ‚ÄúPanorama Pacifico‚Äù (2016) defined the Satin Jackets sound and has now been streamed on Spotify more than 50 million times. Satin Jackets has produced remixes for some of the genre‚Äôs biggest names, including Blank & Jones and Goldroom, and in more recent times has worked closely with bigger artists such as Poolside, Panama, Metaxas and Tycho. 

Opening up the night, all the way from Brooklyn, NY, SUPERTASTE! The trio specializes in their live ensemble performance, instrumentation, and nods to intergenerational funk, disco, and dance music influences. Through yearly retreats to a cabin in Tennessee to hone in their sound, Supertaste has developed a colossal atmosphere of sparkling synths, Chic-inspired guitar riffs, and unforgettable hooks.

Catch Supertaste and Satin Jackets at ZeyZey on November 29th! Tickets on Sale now!

name: Zeyzey And D√©j√†-Vu Present: Simone De Kunovich
description:
For someone who has been digging for obscure records, books and movies since his memory can remember, Simone de Kunovich still transmits the enthusiasm of the beginner. In the past decade he‚Äôs managed to travel the globe far and wide, always on a hunt for blind rarities for his label and Youtube channel Ultimo Tango or playing shows in iconic clubs between London, Tokyo, Paris, New York or his home Milan.

His vast multi-disciplinary knowledge has made him an acclaimed tastemaker, who moves at the crossroads between cinema, music and design, always with a sharp taste for the unconventional. Glimpses of this intense and vast research can be heard in his studio projects, from his last EP on Public Possession, inspired by Y2K dance music and fantasy table games, to the ‚ÄúMondo Nuovo‚Äù trilogy on Mulemusiq, influenced by 70s Exploitation movies and early electronics. In a world of standardisation and predictability, if you love to experience the wonderful of the unexpected, a good way is to catch him doing his thing behind the decks

name: Lost Soul Thanksgiving | Myn And R Gamble
description:
The Marseille-based Parisian Dj and producer MYN runs the esteemed label Public Systems Recordings boasting releases by Beau Wanzer, Kluentah, and many others in the international noise techno scene. As a producer, he has previous releases on Pinkman, Ransom Notes, DJ Loser's Magdalena's Apathy label, and others either solo or as part of a duo. His style is truly genre-defying, tying together all corners of the electronic soundscape as he broadcasts this on his long-standing Rinse France show. He's also showcased his dynamic skills as a selector in renowned clubs like Berghain, Concrete, Rex Club and others.

--

R Gamble is a producer, DJ, and performer based in New York City. Originally from Memphis, TN where he was reared on a strange delta concoction of garage synth-punk, low-fi rap and avant garde experimentation, in NYC he founded the party collective and label Lost Soul Enterprises in 2012. Today he continues to champion dark and weird sounds by DJing and performing live as a longtime resident of Good Room and The Lot Radio. R Gamble has released music on such labels as Mannequin, Public System Recordings, Primitive Languages, Black Lodge, Kraftjerkz, Sisters, Phormix, Fu.Me, Marguerite Records and KRI. He also makes retrofuturistic electro productions under the moniker Drakkar Noir, is one half of industrial duo Fade Accompli along with Myn, and synth-pop duo Zeta Sect with Heidi Sabertooth.

name: Eli Escobar (Open To Close)
description:
With over two decades of electronic music eminence, Eli Escobar has confirmed his place amongst dance music greats. With an unparalleled record collection of handpicked gems and curveball productions, Escobar guides revellers through the heartbeat of music, from the past to the future.
Always looking forward and keeping step with evolving generational tastes, Escobar has redefined his sound in recent years. As an acquainted DJ & Producer, the dance music veteran cut his teeth into the epicentre of 1990‚Äôs New York City hedonism and set the foundations for an admirable career. Releasing music on influential labels such as Phonica, Razor n Tape, Defected‚Äôs ‚ÄòClassic‚Äô and his very own label imprint Night People, only gives a snaps hot into the depth of his discovery. Spanning over more than 20 years, the influence and presence of Eli Escobar is undeniable in every
corner of dance music. As a selector he has appeared on a variety of influential platforms including BBC Radio 1 Esse
ntial Mix, Resident Advisor's Exchange Podcast, Boiler Room, Mixmag ‚ÄòThe Lab‚Äô and The Lot Radio, only to name a few. Likewise transporting his sound to dancefloors across the world with residencies at House of Yes, Le Bain, Battlehymn and beyond. Globally respected and recognised as a forward thinking producer, Escobar‚Äôs output steps beyond conventional dance music with remix work for the likes of Lana Del Rey, M.I.A., Honey Dijon, Cakes Da Killa and many more. Now heading into 2023 Eli looks to stay true to his musical progression with a new EP ‚ÄòTouch Want Feel‚Äô due in May and a full length album in the works for later this year.

 TICKET TIERS: 
The difference between the Tiers is the limited amount of discounted tickets available. Once a tier is sold out the following Tier will be available for purchase. Please plan ahead and buy your tickets in advance. Buying a Pre-Sale ticket will give you priority getting in the party versus buying your ticket at the door.

 ORLANDO HOUSE PARTY GUIDELINES AND MORE INFO...

Any racist, classist, sexist, ableist, body shaming, homophobic or transphobic behavior or harassment of any kind will not be tolerated and is basis for dismissal from the event.

 What Is Orlando House Party?
The goal of Orlando House Party is to create a space where we can disconnect from the rest of the world and all that matters is the present.

name: Subsurface 7 Year Anniversary
address: {'address': '2109 W Glenwood Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19132, USA', 'zip_code': '19132'}
description:
Since December of 2017, it has been one amazing ride. We could've never dreamed of having such an amazing community here in Philadelphia. We thank you for your support over all this time, and as we begin to wrap up another successful year of events, no better way of capping it than celebrating YEAR 7 of this thing we call, Subsurface! 

To help pop off such a special occasion, we welcome some very special guests. First up, a true vet who has held a deep passion for the game for nearly three decades now.. hailing from UK - Truly Madly. After a stellar night at the Dolphin Tavern back in February 2020, we found it he right time to welcome Truly back and show him what Philly warehouse parties are all about. 

In addition, a Chicago native who has made waves playing in renown clubs & venues across the world.. a true digger and purveyor of the dance floor experience, Ricardo Roessel will open up the night for us. 

Last but not least, our resident, John Raffaele, will put a bow on it and close out year 7 in proper fashion deep into that winter morning sunrise. 

See you in the warehouse!!

name: New Year's Eve: Toribio
address: {'address': '2727 W Broad St, Richmond, VA 23220, USA', 'zip_code': '23220'}
description:
NEW YEAR'S EVE @ LOSO w/ TORIBIO
Tuesday, December 31st
Doors: 8pm
DJ Sets: 9pm - 2am
2727 W. Broad St. Richmond, VA 23220
21+

A triple threat who lights up a room when behind the decks, in the studio, and on stage, TORIBIO is a lifelong student of rhythm. Analyzing melodies and chords with a musician's ear, the Dominican-American artist blends different genres and moods in all his creative pursuits-DJing, producing, singing, playing instruments, and even his skills on the mic.

Thanks to a childhood spent playing in church and jazz drumming, the Florida-born, New York-based act has a natural sense of harmony. He takes on the role of musical cartographer in live house fusion band, Conclave, whose debut album was named one of Resident Advisor's best in 2021 and praised by both Rolling Stone and the New Yorker. Acting as the ensemble's bandleader, vocalist, and key instrumentalist, TORIBIO connects jazz, soul, and house from various cultures with style and grace.

His speciality in sonic connections are especially tangible in his DJing. Gliding from pan-Latin club to raw electro to jazz to old-school funk, his sets are a masterclass in building energy and tension. Whether playing Boiler Room or clubs in Mexico City and Tokyo, he knows how to work a crowd with selections and transitions that are as precise as they are powerful. As a producer, his edits and originals are DJ weapons, rinsed by the likes of Gilles Peterson, Rich Medina, and Theo Parrish. His original tracks have been remixed by the likes of Louie Vega, Joe Claussell, and DJ Spinna.

Known for fostering community through movement, his Brooklyn block parties (Public Service NYC) embody the spirit of New York's dance culture while his newly formed imprint B.D.A. is quickly becoming known for bringing these vibes to vinyl. A TORIBIO show is a full-body experience as he always says, "bring dat ass, and your feet will follow.

name: Soul Clap
address: {'address': '2727 W Broad St, Richmond, VA 23220, USA', 'zip_code': '23220'}
description:
SOUL CLAP @ LOSO
Saturday, January 25th
Doors: 8
DJ Sets: 9pm - 2am
2727 W. Broad St. Richmond, VA 23220
21+

Before today there was yesterday and after tomorrow is the future. Lonely C and Bamboozle‚Äôs paths were crossed for all time when a Sun Ra light beam sent from Saturn collided with the P-Funk Mothership and sent them tumbling to earth.  Now, Soul Clap time travels on a musical spaceship of dopeness‚Ä¶

Charles Levine aka Lonely C and Eli Goldstein aka Bamboozle cut their teeth in Boston during the 90‚Äôs rave heyday and quickly learned the power of P.L.U.R., a commitment to PEACE LOVE UNITY & RESPECT in the community, on the dancefloor, and in the DJ booth.  They found an early mentor in Caril Mitro at local record shop Vinyl Connection, who taught them that HOUSE WEARS MANY HATS, ‚Äúthe ethos that the music we love comes in many shapes and sizes‚Äù.  These values have led to a one-of-a-kind take on electronic music that breaks through limitations and genres with a deep commitment to carry on the traditions of our musical foremothers and fathers.

Spreading their wings beyond Boston, Soul Clap found acclaim through a series of edits, remixes and originals on Wolf + Lamb, and became a household name with their mixes of Extravaganza and Bakerman.  They performed everywhere from The Marcy Hotel, to DC10, to Trouw, to Panorama Bar, to The Electric Pickle and on their travels discovered that EVERYBODY‚ÄôS FREAKY UNDERNATURE‚ÄôS KINGDOM.  EFUNK sounds like modern electronic funk and became their calling card, as the title of their first album in 2012, which lead to a collaboration with George Clinton and honorary entry into the P-Funk family.  EFUNK remains a bridge between the discerning futurism of underground dance music and the charisma and boldness of the funk.

EFUNK was followed by contributions to legendary mix series: DJ Kicks, Fabric and Watergate, and a second album, SOUL CLAP in 2016.  Meanwhile they launched Soul Clap Records (which Mixmag called one of the best disco labels of the last decade), joined forces with Wolf + Lamb to found the CREW LOVE collective, and continued to share the knowledge; teaching courses, leading workshops, speaking on panels and always including forgotten classics in their DJ sets.

By harnessing the past Soul Clap looks to the future. After exploring solo ventures, they come back together with a series of EPs beginning with Run It ft. Baby Bam on Classic Music Company and followed by releases on Soul Clap Records and the newly minted EFUNK label.  All leading up to a new Soul Clap album and launch of The Soul Clap Band, whose first incarnation as an eight piece ensemble on the main stage at Movement Detroit was a highlight of 2017.  In anticipation, Soul Clap takes their EFUNK party on the road, growing from Detroit, Miami and New York in 2018 and featuring musical legends of the house, funk and rave worlds.  Always pushing new boundaries, always traveling through time and space, The Clap is on a mission to change the world one dance floor at a time. Dr. Funkenstein has taught us well: free your mind, and your ass will follow.

name: Shaun J. Wright
address: {'address': '2727 W Broad St, Richmond, VA 23220, USA', 'zip_code': '23220'}
description:
Shaun J. Wright @ LOSO
Doors: 8
DJ Sets: 9pm - 2am
2727 W. Broad St. Richmond, VA 23220
21+

Born and raised in west suburban Chicagoland, Shaun J. Wright spent most of their teen years immersed in the sounds of house music. In the late 80‚Äôs and early 90‚Äôs, house music was a powerful force, permeating the mainstream airwaves of Chicago‚Äôs most prominent radio stations. With Wright being raised in the epicenter of house culture during this era, their love for dance music began to expand throughout their high school years as they partook in the underground dance scene now globally known as Juke.

While in undergrad at Morehouse College in Atlanta, Wright developed their skills as a dancer in the vogue ballroom scene and professional dance companies. After acquiring an MA Fashion Curation from the London College of Fashion, Wright enjoyed an active career in fashion in New York City. That is where they met Andrew Butler, founder of Hercules and Love Affair, in 2008, and began a whirlwind collaboration with the ensemble as a vocalist. They spent nearly three years touring with the outfit, performing in major venues & festivals throughout North & South America and Europe. They‚Äôre also featured prominently on the ensemble‚Äôs lauded sophomore album, ‚ÄúBlue Songs‚Äô.

Returning to Chicago in 2012 to forge their solo career, Wright began to collaborate with respected DJ and producer Alinka. Promptly after beginning their party Twirl in the spring of 2013, Wright & Alinka released their first EP, Twirl Vol. 1, on the celebrated Classic Music Company led by luminaries Luke Solomon and Derrick Carter. They continued to expand upon the brand in late 2014 with their Twirl Records debut release ‚ÄúJourney Into The Deep‚Äù EP which included remixes from Kim Ann Foxman and Stereogamous. The label‚Äôs output has received much critical acclaim and has been supported by DJ Mag, XLR8R, Mixmag, BBC Radio 1‚Äôs Heidi and Annie Mac, and a plethora of notable DJ‚Äôs.

name: Suze Ij√≥
address: {'address': '2727 W Broad St, Richmond, VA 23220, USA', 'zip_code': '23220'}
description:
SUZE IJ√ì @ LOSO
Saturday, September 7th
Doors: 8pm
DJ Sets: 9pm - 2am
2727 W. Broad St. Richmond, VA 23220
21+

Suze Ij√≥ is a house DJ. She works in the lineage of that word not just as a name for a genre of dance music, but a mood, a way of moving, an ethic and cultivation of spirit. Ij√≥ grew up in Rotterdam, Europe‚Äôs largest seaport, and was surrounded by hip-hop, Caribbean music and Eurodance ‚Äì products of cultural import and synthesis from the house sounds of Chicago and New York. By the time she was 18, Ij√≥ began going out to clubs with an orientation towards these very sounds; she also started working on local nightlife production teams and as a door host, and later on as a booker. Through these experiences, she developed her taste for the genres she often plays out today: deep-cut RnB, warm and pulsing soul house, interlocking waves of polyrhythms and vocals and timbres all speaking to a profound transhistorical groove.

After beginning to study for a degree in social work, Ij√≥ pivoted to working full-time in music and nightlife: for three years she did sales at Rotterdam‚Äôs Clone records, as well as being part of the former collective First Floor. These days, she curates the podcast series for United Identities along with Carista, and is playing gigs full-time. However close to the heart, her sound has been ringing out in industry-lauded European venues such as Panorama Bar, De School, Lux Frag√≠l, Kaiku and regular slots at Dekmantel Festival; additionally, the last years have seen Ij√≥ make tours of Oceania and South America.

Despite the busy schedule, her club sets reflect an intention and focus granted to each individual space and evening ‚Äì again, this is ‚Äúhouse‚Äù as a feeling, not necessarily a musical structure of BPM-range. Ij√≥ almost always brings incense to her gigs, wrapping the space in a sensual vividnes: her take on the club night is not just a series of DJs showcasing tracks or finesse, but a collective bodily and spiritual event crafted by all those involved, from the bar staff to the crowd to the lighting to the soundsystem. Likely one won‚Äôt have to wait too long before Ij√≥ plays in a club nearby, but luckily, one gets a sense of this even in her numerous radio shows, with broadcasts on NTS, The Lot Radio, and the Dekmantel Podcast series.

PAIGE: Paige‚Äôs DJ sets and productions are a sonic extension of himself. His mission is to take dance floors on a journeythrough genres and emotions, interlinked by a sense of inclusivity, freedom and fun.

With a catalog full of releases on Purified, Odd One Out, and SH√àN, Paige has garnered huge attention from DJs, fans, and key radio figures such as BBC Radio 1‚Äôs Danny Howard, KISS FM, and SiriusXM Chill, where Paige mixes on a monthly basis. From New York to Tulum, Bali to Istanbul, Sao Paulo, Ibiza and beyond, Paige‚Äôs emotive and energetic sets have landed him on club stages around the globe alongside Nora En Pure, Yotto, Cassian, Franky Wah and many more, at legendary venues such as Brooklyn Mirage, Knockdown Center, The Concourse Project, and AME.

name: Signature Sounds Residency X Respekt Music Invite Louie Vega
address: {'address': '1425 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA', 'zip_code': '94103'}
description:
Saturday December 7, 9pm - 2am

Grammy award winning DJ, producer, and remixer Louie Vega is widely recognized as one of the pioneers of house music. As one half of the legendary Masters at Work duo with Kenny "Dope" Gonzalez , Louie Vega has been influential in shaping the global house music scene since the early 90s with his mastery of deep and soulful sounds, seamlessly blending jazz, disco, funk, Latin, soul, African grooves, and more.

Louie Vega‚Äôs musical output has come to define the genres of house and deep house with some of the most iconic voices of the last 30 years including Julie McKnight (Diamond Life), Lisa Fischer (Into My Life / Love Will Know), Arnold Jarvis (Life Goes On), Caron Wheeler (A New Day), and many powerful productions with Anan√©. His remixes have garnered worldwide acclaim, including his reimagining of Curtis Mayfield from 2005-one of seven Grammy nominations, and a win that further cemented his impact on the global scene. While he is a master in the studio, it is behind the DJ decks that his passion for music comes alive-Louie‚Äôs presence is like none other.

The Signature Sounds Residency and Respekt Music are incredibly honored to be hosting Louie Vega in the main warehouse space at The Foundry on Saturday December 7.

In a time of global uncertainty, we invite you all to join us in unity on the dance floor to celebrate dance music culture and pay tribute to the sounds that have brought this community together over the years through love, respect, and kindness.

Local Support:

Lossless Wax
Louiv b2b Philco
Sara Afshar b2b Yanzy

Non Negotiables:

no tolerance for harassment of any kind - if you see something, say something
leave all of your prejudices, biases, problems, and negative energy at the door - we're here for the music selection
no tickets, no entry

Signature Sounds: House, Soul, Funk, and Jazz

Time: Doors open at 9:00 P.M

Address: 1425 Folsom Street

Previous Sets (videos): https://losslesswax.com/sets

If you haven't been to a signature sounds event before we highly encourage you to checkout previous shows to know what you're getting yourselves into.

There is a limited number of tickets. Grab yours ASAP!

All tickets sales are final.

Event is strictly 21+

ABOUT RESPEKT MUSIC:
The mission of Respekt Music is to nurture electronic music by showcasing its depth and variety in its fullest expression and to advance the public appreciation of this art form and the adjacent arts of music production, DJ mixing, lighting and digital visualizations. Respektmusic.co

name: Baltra - Charlotte
address: {'address': '645 Florida Ave NW #7, Washington, DC 20001, USA', 'zip_code': '20001'}
description:
Saturday, December 14, 2024
Doors 10PM

Advance Tickets on sale now.

Born and raised in Philadelphia but currently based in New York, Baltra has spent the last decade honing a sound that‚Äôs rich both in romance and melancholy. And always with warm, nostalgic melodies.

Releasing his first music in parallel with the lo-fi house explosion of the mid-2010s alongside artists such as Mall Grab, Ross From Friends and DJ Seinfeld, Baltra racked up millions of plays across YouTube and key streaming services with definitive releases on Step Rec., IDNK (I Do Not Know), Tape Throb Records, Shall Not Fade‚Äôs sub-label Lost Palms, Of Paradise as well as his own 96 and Forever Records imprints.

Baltra has always had an unstoppable approach and attention to detail that‚Äôs set him apart from so many of his production peers. Often using his own voice, or that of collaborators such as Park Hye Jin, rather than relying on samples, he explored both higher and lower tempos on his 2019 debut album ‚ÄòTed‚Äô. 2021 saw him release two highly acclaimed EPs on Local Action (Ambition) that had remixes from Yazzus Remix, Martyn Bootyspoon, CFCF, Ariel Zetina and Wawa as well as on Bristol-based label Shall Not Fade (Dreaming Of A Disco), respectively.

The first half of 2023 has seen him return with his ‚ÄòWhere I End‚Äô mixtape which was released via the label head‚Äôs very own 96 And Forever Records that came out of the digital gates with top tier Spotify, Apple Music, and Deezer playlist placement as well as covers, support from Mixmag, DJ Mag, The Ransom Note, and key dance radio support on BB stations Radio 1 and 6 Music as well as Rinse FM and KEXP. 2023 has also seen him remix ‚ÄòGus Dapperton ‚Äì Horizons‚Äô on Warner and ‚ÄòDJ Q & Todd Edwards ‚Äì Sweet Day‚Äô on Local Action with upcoming remixes of ‚ÄòMafro ‚Äì Bloom‚Äô on Virgin Music‚Äôs sub-label LG105, and the remix package for his mixtape ‚ÄòWhere I End‚Äô which includes tracks from Scuba, Jaquese Greene, DJ Q, and Guava.

Born in the South of France but native of Carg√®se in Corsica, Charlotte knows an exponential trajectory on the electronic stage of the South of France. Her inspirations come mainly from the underground music of Romania. Aged only 18 years old, she started playing in the Polikarpov Bar in Marseille, in N√Æmes too. She also inaugurated the ‚ÄúTechno Wednesday‚Äù at the Mistral in Aix-en-Provence and also at Spartacus Club. But it‚Äôs playing at the Cargese Sound System Festival last summer that she passed a new step in her DJ career. After this show, she played for the first time in Paris. Now, she regularly plays at La dame Noir in Marseille, one of the best electronic music clubs in the South of France.

Paris's university seems not to have lost any of its superb when it comes to electronic music. Its persistent lights keep attracting -as much as they steadily arouse- more and more artists from the country towards her, although a very few, the most cunning ones succeed in implanting durably there.

Under IRM founders‚Äô friendly wings, who noticed in the first place his talent, and some expert producers friends and encouraging critic, the young producer keep on working and delivering new material, easily oscillating between genres, that has already convinced most of the electronic scene's god-fathers.

The Frenchman‚Äôs discography pledges for his dynamism: in a few of years he proved his versatility, composing a cold, fierce, uncompromising techno as well as a melodious, jazzy deep house, suave and delicately bouncing. Traumer's musical circumvolutions reflect the deepness of his creativity and his technical mastering. Alternating genres, switching from smooth, sensible productions to straight, ecstatic techno tracks, he succeeded in building up a rich and strong repertoire, giving his live performances an unanimous acclamation in prestigious clubs like Paris's Rex and allowing him the notable supports of artists.

name: Ivan Smagghe - Sarah Wreath
address: {'address': '645 Florida Ave NW #7, Washington, DC 20001, USA', 'zip_code': '20001'}
description:
Saturday, November 30, 2024
Doors 10PM

Advance Tickets on sale now.

Ivan Smagghe belongs to a top table of DJs that journalists like to lazily describe as ‚ÄúThe DJ‚Äôs DJ‚Äù. He has the ability to play music like a raw conduit between famously obscure records whilst never losing sight of the dancefloor‚Äôs strobe soaked bodies - injecting something of himself seamlessly into the mix along the way.

His genre defying/defining production from Black Strobe, It‚Äôs A Fine Line and now Smagghe & Cross has connected him and garnered the praise from the likes of Craig Richards, Vladimir Ivkovic, Paranoid London, Optimo, Solar and of course, his long time friend Andrew Weatherall - all fellow crusaders in the fight to prove that electronic music is so much more than a one dimensional soundtrack for a night on the lash, and so much more than an Instagram account. In January 2020, Smagghe & Cross released their second LP, 1819, on Offen Music and just released a new LP at the end of 2023.

After co-running the legendary french label and parties, ‚ÄúKill The DJ,‚Äù Ivan washeading up his own imprint, ‚ÄúLes Disques De La Mort‚Äù; an outlet for a unique taste in music and spanning releases & remixes from long staples (Manfredas, Cosmo Vitelli, Marco Passarani, I-Cube, Red Axes, Roman Fluegel) & special newcomers (Elles, Sworn Virgins, Zillas on Acid). LDDLM is a label that is always faithful to an instinctively recognisable ‚Äústyle of no style‚Äù and the refusal to be pigeonholed. Covid has reframed the way of making and diffusing music : whilst thinking of reactivating some label action, Ivan has opened Amor Fati with Niv Arzi from Red Axes, a counterintuitive blog page giving away edits to whoever wants them. The collaboration between these two may take form in Customs & Faces, a new outlet and an Axes x Smagghe 12‚Äù will be out before the summer on Animals Dancing.

You can catch Ivan subverting the masses any given weekend in clubs & festivals such as Lux/Lisbon, Nitsa/Barcelona, Rex/Paris, In Between/Los Angeles, Corsica Studios/London, Nuits Sonores/Lyon, Love International/Croatia, Houghton/Norfolk and many other dens of iniquity worldwide.


Berlin-based DJ, sound practitioner, and sound engineer Sarah Wreath is dedicated to harnessing the transformative power of music. Focused on exploring frequencies, sound research, and music production, she embraces the alchemical properties of sound to create immersive experiences.

Versatility is key to her style, as she seamlessly navigates a wide range of genres. Taking listeners on a journey through space and texture, her music shifts from grooving, classy techno to psychedelic-leaning sounds and ambient soundscapes, creating an energy that feels both transcendent and grounded, resonating through body and mind. Tribal rhythms, modular synths, and a touch of experimentation define her unique sonic signature. Her LP Integration, released through The Bunker New York, showcases her commitment to immersive rhythms and sonic exploration.

name: Enzo Siragusa
address: {'address': '645 Florida Ave NW #7, Washington, DC 20001, USA', 'zip_code': '20001'}
description:
Saturday, December 7, 2024
Doors 10PM

Advance Tickets on sale now.

When it comes to rave culture there aren‚Äôt many artists out there who are as passionate and dedicated as Enzo Siragusa. Fully immersed in the rave movement which swept Britain in the early ‚Äô90s, the Londoner still holds true many of the aspects of that storied era, weaving them through his ambitious ventures, including FUSE which has long been ranked as one of London‚Äôs most revered brands. So, whether he‚Äôs DJing, making bass heavy cuts in the studio, steering record labels or hosting sellout events, it‚Äôs guaranteed to be fueled by a desire to perpetuate the culture that changed his life.

Enzo‚Äôs first rave was at the legendary Sanctuary in Milton Keynes in 1993, where cult raves like Dreamscape and Helter Skelter were held. His experiences there left an indelible impression on him; from the power of the music and the sound systems, to the experience of being connected to a diverse yet unified crowd. This formed the foundation of his ongoing ethos; maintaining an equal balance between 1) music and sound, 2) a strong sense of community and 3) the environment, i.e the club itself. These three core aspects are the pillars of Enzo‚Äôs rave philosophy and undoubtedly what have made it so successful.

The catalyst behind his early forays into DJing was a healthy obsession with music which led to a very expensive vinyl addiction, one that‚Äôs still stacked with house, techno, and UK bass heavy sounds across drum and bass, garage and jungle. Over 20 years on and he‚Äôs a world-respected DJ, one whose enthusiasm remains resolute, and one whose shrewd selections have reverberated through hallowed clubs such as London‚Äôs fabric and Printworks, Berlin‚Äôs Panorama Bar, Leeds‚Äô Mint Warehouse, Space Miami, Paris‚Äô Rex Club, Frankfurt‚Äôs Robert Johnson and Manchester‚Äôs Warehouse Project.

With the launch of event series E:DIMENSION, his next passion project, Enzo loops back to his early DJing years of playing extended sets. Never losing sight of his raving days in the ‚Äô90s, when crowds would feverishly follow one DJ all night, he has consistently injected a taste of this era through his output over the years, including his recent sell-out All Night Long sessions at fabric, one of which was an impetus for the creation of E:DIMENSION. Opening at Printworks, the events see a reinvigorated Enzo again pay homage to his roots while kicking off a whole new chapter. He stands to bag further opportunity to push his musical boundaries and connect with music heads on a deeper level as he centers long sets, the art of DJING and the journey element of airing a genre hopping record collection that spans decades.
